\n< Serena >Lady Mary... Ah, oh my, um... I apologize for

\n< Mary >Oh my, calling it an interruption... Serena-chan,

\n< Mary >Yes, it's really tough... but more than that,
she's even more adorable, you know...

drinking milk like this...

\n< Mary >I feel like I was born to meet this child. That's

\n< Mary >For now, you see.

\n< Serena >Um... Mary-sama, if I may ask... does it not hurt

\n< Serena >Huh?

must be confused by all the changes happening to
her body, right?

\n< Serena >Lately, my chest has been hurting... I wonder if
I'm sick...

\n< Mary >Hehehe, don't worry. That's normal. It means
Serena-chan is also getting ready to breastfeed a
baby like this.

\n< Serena >Breast milk... will it come out? Could it be that
pain...!?

\n< Mary >Ahh, umm. It's not like it comes out right away.
Breast milk naturally starts to come out after the
baby is born, you know.
\n< Serena >I-I see...

\n< Mary >The preparations for that have already begun
inside Serena- chan's body. It means you're
growing up. It means you're ready to become a
mother.
\n< Serena >To become an adult...

\n< Mary >So, there's no need to panic. It's natural to be
surprised at first. It happens to everyone.
\n< Serena >....

\n< Mary >Breasts are for the baby. Right now, Serena-
chan's breasts are working hard for the sake of
future babies.
\n< Mary >So please take good care of them.
\n< Serena >Specifically, what should I do...?

\n< Mary >Don't touch them too much. Just because it feels
good, doesn't mean you should play with them.
\n< Serena >It doesn't feel good, but...

\n< Mary >Next is choosing underwear. It's best to choose
something that tightly wraps around your breasts.
It may be expensive though...

\n< Serena >Yes, I did buy some, but they just don't feel
right...

\n< Mary >It may feel strange at first, but you'll get used
to it quickly.

\n< Mary >And also, make sure to wear something that fits
your body properly. As your body grows, your
breasts will also become bigger, so it's better to
consult with a trusted adult about it.
\n< Serena >To an adult person... Hmm.

\n< Mary >But when it still hurts no matter what, you should
pray to God.
\n< Serena >To God?
\n< Mary >Yes. Thank you for making my body grow every day.

\n< Mary >Because that pain is like a sign from God, saying
that it's okay to give birth to a baby and be
happy.

\n< Mary >Well, if you do that, well, it will be painful...
but you'll stop worrying about it. You'll
understand that it's not a bad pain.
\n< Serena >I see...

\n< Serena >It was helpful. It was really helpful. Thank you,
Mary.
\n< Mary >No, you're welcome.
\n< Serena >Well.
\n< Mary >Oh, are you leaving already?

\n< Serena >Yes. There are still things I need to do. My
worries have disappeared, so now it's time for
work.
\n< Mary >Yes, then please come again.
\n< Serena >Ah, well then, see you again.
\n< Mary >Please come again, Serena-chan.

\n< Mary >Serena-san... I heard. I can only pray for you,
but please come back safely...
\n< Serena >Excuse me--.
\n< Female >Oh my! Welcome! Welcome, little adventurer!
\n< Serena >Ah, ah...
\n< Serena >It's good to see you're doing well.

\n< Mary >Wha...what...uh, umm.

\n< Mary >The baby, you know? When a man and a woman really,
really love each other, they think about each
other a lot and...

\n< Mary >The stamen and pistil...they come

\n< Serena >Huh?

\n< Mary >Anyway, anyway, you know? The crystallization of
love between a man and a woman is a baby.

\n< Mary >At first, it's much smaller... Women take a lot of
time to slowly and gradually raise the baby,
making it grow bigger.

\n< Mary >Well, you see, it's very difficult... but it's
something that has a lot of value. It's the most
valuable thing in this world.
\n< Serena >It has value...?

\n< Mary >Well, you see...that's right, isn't it? I was also
born because my mom and dad loved each other.

\n< Mary >My mom and dad were also born because their moms
and dads loved each other.

\n< Mary >Even my father's father's father and my mother's
mother's mother's mother...

\n< Mary >From a time so long ago that it feels like my mind
is drifting away... I love you, I cherish you.
That's how I feel.

\n< Mary >It has been transmitted without interruption even
once.
\n< Mary >And then my husband was born, and I was born...

\n< Mary >And then, we love each other, saying I love you.
We give birth to a child and pass on that love to
them.
\n< Mary >I love you, I cherish you.

\n< Mary >...This child will surely pass it on to their
children someday. And their children will continue
to pass it on, forever and ever.
\n< Mary >That's why the whole world is made of love.
\n< Mary >I'm so, so happy... I'm glad you're here.

\n< Mary >People give birth to and raise children in order
to convey those feelings to each other.
\n< Serena >Me too...?
\n< Mary >Of course!

\n< Mary >Serena-chan, me, and everyone else, we are all in

\n< Mary >Saying I love you and I cherish you a lot is what
made you, Serena-chan, into Serena- chan.

\n< Mary >Because if it wasn't like that, you wouldn't have
become such an adorable Serena- chan.

\n< Mary >That's why Serena-chan, too, has a big love and I
love you, I cherish you.

\n< Mary >And someday, I will have someone I want to convey
it to, and children I want to convey it to.
\n< Serena >I see...
\n< Serena >...I've never thought about it that way before.

\n< Serena >I used to think that children are born out of
obligation.

\n< Serena >In order to continue the family and leave behind
blood, my father and mother created me for that

\n< Serena >Well, in my family, there is already my older

there.

\n< Serena >That's why I thought about how I can fulfill my

\n< Mary >Serena-chan.
\n< Serena >Huh?
\n< Mary >That is absolutely, absolutely, absolutely wrong.

\n< Mary >No parent thinks that having a child and raising
them is an obligation.

\n< Mary >When I was still my father and mother's daughter,
I didn't understand it well either.

\n< Mary >But now that I've become a mother to this child, I
understand. I can say this much.

\n< Mary >Children are pure joy for parents. They are love
itself. For the sake of their smiles, for the sake
of their happiness, parents are willing to
sacrifice their bodies, their lives, and even
their souls without hesitation.
\n< Mary >So, you know? Please don't say such things...

\n< Mary >Sometimes parents may not be able to express it
well, but always, no matter when, they think about
their children... mmm...!
\n< Serena >Lady Mary?
\n< Mary >Ouch... th-tha...that. What is this... I wonder...

\n< Mary >Maybe I got a little tired from talking so
much...?
